    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "8, 234–235, 244 of family, 258–265 filler words, 219–220 finding scenes, 78–87 flashbacks, 150–152, 155–157, 159–160, 168, 169 flowery language, 210–211 foundation of, 50–70 humor in, 116–130, 144 ``` ``` ideas for stories, 15–16, 23–24, 27–49, 60, 303–304, 309–310 inciting incidents, 32–34, 49 job interviews and, 38, 77–78 jump cuts, 72, 74, 110 lens, 68–69, 164–168, 220–221, 242, 281, 310 main event, 84–85, 104–107, 160–163, 189, 270 materials for, 71–110 memories, mining for, 27–49 mistakes and, 43–49 moments, giving space to, 81–85 narrative stepping stones, 71–78, 110 nerves, 197, 226–234, 244 one sentence, 68–69, 70, 95, 110, 206, 252, 301–302 onstage, 193–222, 223–244 out-of-the-ordinary events, 31–33 outlines, 16, 72 perspective, 124, 131–132, 152, 220–221, 316 point of view, 69, 100, 168 prompts, 15, 28–29, 32, 36, 53, 54, 252, 255, 261–262, 298– 299, 303–304 ``` ``` pronouns, 217–218 punchlines, 120, 121, 128–129 repetition, 209–210 resolution, 105–110 reviewing, 301–302 ripple effect of, 247–271 salty language, 211–213 saying out loud, 201–202, 213–215, 222 at school, 248–253 shifts in perspective and, 35–38, 67 smaller story, carrying weight of larger, 160–163, 169 SNAFU, 55–56 social settings, 30, 62, 98–99, 206 stakes, 14, 51–52, 54–59, 66, 70, 73, 177, 206, 214, 301 structure and, 145–169 tense, use of, 207–209, 222 tension, 51–52, 54, 59, 84, 104, 125–126, 148, 153, 214 themes, 7, 18, 62, 64, 98, 219 timing of, 14, 17, 203–207, 216 toasts (see toasts) ``` ``` transformation, 14, 65–67, 266, 282 truth in, 9–10, 14, 99–101 vulnerability, 19, 48, 111, 114, 116–117, 215, 227, 234, 254– 256, 316 at work, 253–258 of world, 265–271 StorySLAM, 14, 17, 18–23, 67, 112, 201, 305, 307, 312–313 rules of, 18–23 \"Stumbling in the Dark\" (Turturro), 34 summaries, 74–77 Summerville, Stephanie, 188 \"Surviving Comrade Stalin\" (Levenstein), 176 Suzuki, Wendy, 53, 97 T Tana, Gaby, 7 Taste the Nation (documentary), xiv Teller, 226 Tellers, Kate, 18, 46, 67, 125, 140, 145, 221, 229, 233–234, 254 tense, use of, 207–209, 222 ``` ``` tension, 51–52, 54, 59, 84, 104, 125–126, 148, 153, 214 \"Test, The\" (Soskin), 180 \"That Thing on My Arm\" (Lakshmi), 90 Thau, Lea, 148, 315 themes, 7, 18, 62, 64, 98, 219 \"Theory of Change\" (Jamison), 208 \"Things Left Unsaid\" (McNally), 42–43 \"This Is Going to Suck\" (Dicks), 79 Thomas, R.",
    "char_count": 2347,
    "refiner_needed": false
