  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_b4dd9975",
    "title": "OUR GUIDE TO GETTING STARTED",
    "section": "OUR GUIDE TO GETTING STARTED",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "[U](#page-331-0) [V](#page-332-0) [W](#page-332-1) [X](#page-333-0) [Y](#page-333-1) Z\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# HOW\n\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# TO TELL\n\n\nYOUR STORY\n\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# OUR GUIDE TO GETTING STARTED\n\nThese are tools we've used to help people around the world take that first, sometimes difficult step toward developing a story. Jot down ideas, big and small—no judgments allowed! Use the pages below to find and refine your story (and all your stories going forward). And remember, stories are meant to be shared!\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# FINDING YOUR STORY\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 623,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_48f28023",
    "title": "<span id=\"page-337-0\"></span>STORY IDEAS",
    "section": "FINDING YOUR STORY",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "ages below to find and refine your story (and all your stories going forward). And remember, stories are meant to be shared!\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# FINDING YOUR STORY\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n#### <span id=\"page-337-0\"></span>STORY IDEAS\n\nHere are some prompts to get you started. See if you can complete any—or all—of them. (If you have more than one answer to a prompt, list them all!)\n\nI will never forget the time when…\n\nA moment I surprised myself was when…\n\nIf my life were a movie, one unforgettable scene would be…\n\nA decision I made that changed everything was…\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 607,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_9e87dfca",
    "title": "PAINTING A SCENE",
    "section": "PAINTING A SCENE",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "ever forget the time when…\n\nA moment I surprised myself was when…\n\nIf my life were a movie, one unforgettable scene would be…\n\nA decision I made that changed everything was…\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# PAINTING A SCENE\n\n<span id=\"page-338-0\"></span>Take one of your responses to the prompts and re-create the scene or moment it took place. Note the setting, the season, the room where it happened, the song on the radio…. Don't forget to include how you felt both physically (the thumping of your heart or the sweat on your brow) and emotionally (red hot mad or cool and calm, deep in love or ready to walk).\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 637,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_b99b52c6",
    "title": "REVIEWING YOUR STORY",
    "section": "REVIEWING YOUR STORY",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "to include how you felt both physically (the thumping of your heart or the sweat on your brow) and emotionally (red hot mad or cool and calm, deep in love or ready to walk).\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# REVIEWING YOUR STORY\n\n<span id=\"page-339-0\"></span>Remember, stories take time to develop. The same story can be told in myriad ways. Once you're ready to tell your story, keep the following checklist in mind.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# 1. What's your \"one sentence\"?\n\nCan you distill—in one sentence—what the story is ultimately about for you?\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 578,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_9ebb67c4",
    "title": "2. Is the change clear?",
    "section": "2. Is the change clear?",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "ep the following checklist in mind.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# 1. What's your \"one sentence\"?\n\nCan you distill—in one sentence—what the story is ultimately about for you?\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# 2. Is the change clear?\n\nDo you clearly express the difference between who you were at the beginning of the story and who you were at the end?\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 373,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_d07b41fb",
    "title": "3. Are the stakes defined?",
    "section": "3. Are the stakes defined?",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "# 2. Is the change clear?\n\nDo you clearly express the difference between who you were at the beginning of the story and who you were at the end?\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# 3. Are the stakes defined?\n\nIs your listener clear on what you stood to gain or lose? Why was it important? Who or what was standing in your way?\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 347,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_e7da5a69",
    "title": "4. Can you identify your arc?",
    "section": "4. Can you identify your arc?",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "# 3. Are the stakes defined?\n\nIs your listener clear on what you stood to gain or lose? Why was it important? Who or what was standing in your way?\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# 4. Can you identify your arc?\n\n- Do you clearly articulate the necessary backstory and context?\n- Do you include an inciting incident (the thing that broke the pattern)?\n- Have you built tension in your story? How?\n- What is the resolution? Do you stick your landing?\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 472,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_29d47591",
    "title": "5. Have you balanced scenes and summary?",
    "section": "5. Have you balanced scenes and summary?",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "?\n- Do you include an inciting incident (the thing that broke the pattern)?\n- Have you built tension in your story? How?\n- What is the resolution? Do you stick your landing?\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# 5. Have you balanced scenes and summary?\n\n- Are there moments that could be built out into a larger scene with more details?\n- Would the story flow better if some of the scenes were summarized?\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 424,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_27bdda19",
    "title": "6. Is your story the correct length for your audience?",
    "section": "6. Is your story the correct length for your audience?",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": " scenes and summary?\n\n- Are there moments that could be built out into a larger scene with more details?\n- Would the story flow better if some of the scenes were summarized?\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# 6. Is your story the correct length for your audience?\n\n- Is there a time limit, and if so, can you tell your story within it?\n- If it is running long, can it be trimmed or adjusted? (Hint: Look for two sentences that could be told in one. Try to find any redundancies that could be shortened, summarized, or completely edited out.)\n\nIf it is too short, is there anything you might consider adding? (Hint: Look for a moment that could be turned into a larger scene. Find places to add details about your state of mind.)\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 750,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_47aba827",
    "title": "7. Does your \"one sentence\" still apply?",
    "section": "7. Does your \"one sentence\" still apply?",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": " short, is there anything you might consider adding? (Hint: Look for a moment that could be turned into a larger scene. Find places to add details about your state of mind.)\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# 7. Does your \"one sentence\" still apply?\n\nAfter considering these questions, do you feel all of the pieces of your story support your \"one sentence\"?\n\nIf you've checked off everything on this list, find a supportive friend and take your story for a test run!\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 489,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_cc110205",
    "title": "STORY PROMPTS",
    "section": "STORY PROMPTS",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "eel all of the pieces of your story support your \"one sentence\"?\n\nIf you've checked off everything on this list, find a supportive friend and take your story for a test run!\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# STORY PROMPTS\n\n<span id=\"page-341-0\"></span>Need some more help finding your story? Here are some themes and prompts to get you started. Choose one prompt and see where it takes you. There are no wrong answers! The stories are yours!\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 464,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_b1c4fca9",
    "title": "FIRSTS",
    "section": "STORY PROMPTS",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "elp finding your story? Here are some themes and prompts to get you started. Choose one prompt and see where it takes you. There are no wrong answers! The stories are yours!\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n#### FIRSTS\n\nTell us about a breakthrough moment.\n\nTell us about a first time that you regretted.\n\nTell us about a first time that changed your life.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 378,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_9c5b06b0",
    "title": "NINE TO FIVE",
    "section": "STORY PROMPTS",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "#### FIRSTS\n\nTell us about a breakthrough moment.\n\nTell us about a first time that you regretted.\n\nTell us about a first time that changed your life.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n#### NINE TO FIVE\n\nTell us about a time you worked hard and played hard.\n\nTell us about a time you were working for the weekend.\n\nTell us about a time you didn't see eye-to-eye with management.\n\nTell us about a time you definitely weren't being paid enough.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 462,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_b6386770",
    "title": "LOVE HURTS",
    "section": "STORY PROMPTS",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "out a time you were working for the weekend.\n\nTell us about a time you didn't see eye-to-eye with management.\n\nTell us about a time you definitely weren't being paid enough.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n#### LOVE HURTS\n\nTell us about a time it was too little, too late.\n\nTell us about a time you had to follow your heart.\n\nTell us about a time you loved and lost.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 389,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_acccdfec",
    "title": "CAUGHT",
    "section": "STORY PROMPTS",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "#### LOVE HURTS\n\nTell us about a time it was too little, too late.\n\nTell us about a time you had to follow your heart.\n\nTell us about a time you loved and lost.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n#### CAUGHT\n\nTell us about a time you were busted.\n\nTell us about a time you wove a tangled web.\n\nTell us about a time your hand was in the cookie jar.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 367,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_c8ca457b",
    "title": "LOST AND FOUND",
    "section": "STORY PROMPTS",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "#### CAUGHT\n\nTell us about a time you were busted.\n\nTell us about a time you wove a tangled web.\n\nTell us about a time your hand was in the cookie jar.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n#### LOST AND FOUND\n\nTell us about a time you couldn't see what was right in front of you.\n\nTell us about a time you couldn't find a way out.\n\nTell us about a time you were reunited with something you treasure.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 417,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_fd5a3bb0",
    "title": "<span id=\"page-343-0\"></span>HOW TO HOST A MOTH-STYLE STORYTELLING GATHERING",
    "section": "<span id=\"page-343-0\"></span>HOW TO HOST A MOTH-STYLE STORYTELLING GATHERING",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "time you couldn't see what was right in front of you.\n\nTell us about a time you couldn't find a way out.\n\nTell us about a time you were reunited with something you treasure.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# <span id=\"page-343-0\"></span>HOW TO HOST A MOTH-STYLE STORYTELLING GATHERING\n\nIf you haven't attended a Moth StorySLAM, we hope you'll try it sometime! See link on page 311 to find an event in your area. But even if you can't make it to The Moth, perhaps you'll consider throwing your own event—in your home, your workplace, at Grandma's eightieth birthday, around a campfire, or on a long bus trip. No special equipment is necessary…just open-hearted listeners and if you want to get fancy, a microphone.\n\nYou have been volleying stories back and forth all your life. This gathering can be a fun way to hear more and share more, and for people to get five glorious uninterrupted minutes on your homemade \"stage.\" All the loving ears on the story might just be the best thing to happen to your guests all week.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 1041,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_c019b86c",
    "title": "PICK A THEME",
    "section": "<span id=\"page-343-0\"></span>HOW TO HOST A MOTH-STYLE STORYTELLING GATHERING",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": " people to get five glorious uninterrupted minutes on your homemade \"stage.\" All the loving ears on the story might just be the best thing to happen to your guests all week.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n#### PICK A THEME\n\nSo many to choose from! If you're having an intimate gathering of people who already know each other or have a person or a passion in common, you might have a custom theme.\n\nExample: Paolo's fortieth birthday. Theme: *Your Escapades with Paolo*. (See tips for telling stories at birthday celebrations on page 85.)\n\nNo matter who is invited, you'll want a theme that will inspire a broad range of stories. Whenever The Moth launches a StorySLAM in a new city, we begin with the theme FIRSTS. People tend to remember firsts and no matter who you are, you've had a thousand, so there should be no shortage of material.\n\nHere is the prompt we use for FIRSTS:\n\n*Prepare a story about your maiden voyage into uncharted territory. Wax on about your first: standing ovation, miserable failure, kiss, child, crisis of conscience, job, pet, toupee, trip overseas, exorcism, internet date, grandchild, or fist fight. Grand openings, birth order, wild initiations, or milestones reached.*\n\n(This prompt and a hundred more are also part of A Game of Storytelling, The Moth's deck of cards, available at our website, themoth.org.)\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 1364,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_8d3132fe",
    "title": "INVITE THE PEOPLE",
    "section": "<span id=\"page-343-0\"></span>HOW TO HOST A MOTH-STYLE STORYTELLING GATHERING",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "tiations, or milestones reached.*\n\n(This prompt and a hundred more are also part of A Game of Storytelling, The Moth's deck of cards, available at our website, themoth.org.)\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n#### INVITE THE PEOPLE\n\nTell your guests that everyone is invited to share a five-minute (or less!) true story and let them know the theme in advance so they can percolate on ideas.\n\nSome shy folks may balk at this. Tell them it's okay if they don't want to speak, but *definitely* check in and encourage them once the stories start flowing. (Many alleged wallflowers have knocked our socks off with powerful stories when cheered on!)\n\nInclude a link to our \"Storytelling Guidelines\" webpage for best practices, tips, and rules. Suggest that your guests tune into *The Moth Radio Hour* or *The Moth* podcast for inspiration. Again, see themoth.org.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 877,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_6ae1b30a",
    "title": "PREPARING FOR THE GATHERING",
    "section": "<span id=\"page-343-0\"></span>HOW TO HOST A MOTH-STYLE STORYTELLING GATHERING",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "delines\" webpage for best practices, tips, and rules. Suggest that your guests tune into *The Moth Radio Hour* or *The Moth* podcast for inspiration. Again, see themoth.org.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n#### PREPARING FOR THE GATHERING\n\n- Have enough seats for everyone, or cushions so any extras can get comfortable on the floor.\n- Create a space at the front of the room for each teller to share their story. If they are able to stand, ask them to stand. (It makes a difference!)\n- <span id=\"page-344-0\"></span>Turn off the TV, the radio, the computer (of course!).\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 593,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_602a494e",
    "title": "DETERMINE THE HOST",
    "section": "<span id=\"page-343-0\"></span>HOW TO HOST A MOTH-STYLE STORYTELLING GATHERING",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "are their story. If they are able to stand, ask them to stand. (It makes a difference!)\n- <span id=\"page-344-0\"></span>Turn off the TV, the radio, the computer (of course!).\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n#### DETERMINE THE HOST\n\nYour gathering needs a host to get everyone on the same page and keep things moving. Will it be you or will you assign the role to a charming friend or associate? The host will welcome everyone, explain what's about\n\nto happen, detail a few guidelines, and then welcome the tellers up, picking their names at random, one at a time. The host might want to razzle-dazzle in a top hat or be a quieter presence who guides the night. Up to you!\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 693,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_f25229b4",
    "title": "CAMARADERIE OR COMPETITION?",
    "section": "<span id=\"page-343-0\"></span>HOW TO HOST A MOTH-STYLE STORYTELLING GATHERING",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": " their phones. If you have a large group, you might want to clarify that you'll be picking only ten names from the hat because a night of fifteen stories is a loooong night.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n#### CAMARADERIE OR COMPETITION?\n\nA night of stories, told up close and personal, is beautiful on its own. Leave it there. But some people love competition. They want to win and it motivates them to follow the rules. So maybe you'd like to award a prize to the night's favorite storyteller (a home-cooked meal, a handmade newspaper crown, a handful of loose change, a banana). You could pick three judges, or two, or just decide yourself. Our advice is to keep any judging especially kind. Stories are tender and personal. \"Losing\" at storytelling can feel like an indictment of your character, so make sure everyone who doesn't win the coveted victory banana feels like a runner up.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 912,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_753d1a81",
    "title": "HAVE FUN, BUT HAVE KLEENEX",
    "section": "<span id=\"page-343-0\"></span>HOW TO HOST A MOTH-STYLE STORYTELLING GATHERING",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "nd personal. \"Losing\" at storytelling can feel like an indictment of your character, so make sure everyone who doesn't win the coveted victory banana feels like a runner up.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n#### HAVE FUN, BUT HAVE KLEENEX\n\nSome stories might get intense. You may learn things about the people you've gathered that you never knew before…. Your heart may open up in unexpected ways and tears may flow. Also, their story may open you up and inspire you to share yours one day.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 512,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_67e64503",
    "title": "LIVE EVENTS",
    "section": "FOR MORE STORIES",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "tory: Call, or visit [themoth.org](http://themoth.org/) and pitch right on our website. Pitch away! We can't wait to meet you.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# FOR MORE STORIES\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n#### LIVE EVENTS\n\nVisit our website, [themoth.org/events](http://themoth.org/events) to find shows near you, including local open-mic Moth StorySLAMs, where you can throw your name in the hat for a chance to tell your story.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 453,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_3fec4eb6",
    "title": "PLAYLIST OF FEATURED STORIES",
    "section": "FOR MORE STORIES",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "vents](http://themoth.org/events) to find shows near you, including local open-mic Moth StorySLAMs, where you can throw your name in the hat for a chance to tell your story.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n#### PLAYLIST OF FEATURED STORIES\n\nVisit our website, [themoth.org/storyplaylist](http://themoth.org/storyplaylist) for a playlist of the stories featured in this book. We hope they will inspire you to share a few of your own!\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:SKIP -->\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 478,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_fbe4ba5d",
