    "text": "# Available from THE MOTH\n\n\n\"Stories that attest to . . . the shared threads of love, loss, fear and kindness that connect us.\"\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# -MICHIKO KAKUTANI, The New York Times\n\n\nRead more stories in The Moth's first collection, *The Moth: 50 True Stories*\n\n\nA *New York Times* bestseller including stories by Malcolm Gladwell, Sebastian Junger, Annie Duke, Joyce Maynard, Nathan Englander, and more\n\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# Also available from the storytelling experts at\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 524,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_f175821c",
    "title": "THE MOTH",
    "section": "THE MOTH",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "s by Malcolm Gladwell, Sebastian Junger, Annie Duke, Joyce Maynard, Nathan Englander, and more\n\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# Also available from the storytelling experts at\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# THE MOTH\n\n\nA Game of Storytelling is an interactive card deck that uses true stories to encourage lively conversations, spark creativity, and improve your public speaking abilities.\n\n\nAvailable wherever books are sold\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n# RANDOM HOUSE BOOK CLUB\n\nBecause Stories Are Better Shared\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n#### Discover\n\nExciting new books that spark conversation every week.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n#### Connect\n\nWith authors on tour—or in your living room. (Request an Author Chat for your book club!)\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n#### **Discuss**\n\nStories that move you with fellow book lovers on Facebook, on Goodreads, or at in-person meet-ups.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
    "char_count": 911,
    "refiner_needed": false
  },
  {
    "id": "How to Tell a Story_44d03129",
    "title": "Enhance",
    "section": "RANDOM HOUSE BOOK CLUB",
    "source": "How to Tell a Story",
    "text": "or Chat for your book club!)\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n#### **Discuss**\n\nStories that move you with fellow book lovers on Facebook, on Goodreads, or at in-person meet-ups.\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->\n\n#### **Enhance**\n\nYour reading experience with discussion prompts, digital book club kits, and more, available on our website.\n\nJoin our online book club community!\n\ngrandomhousebookclub.com\n\nRandom House Book Club\n\nBecause Stories Are Better Shared\n\nRANDOM HOUSE\n\n\n<!-- BOUNDARY:CONTENT -->",
